From de31f37472b9396f8465b9f5aa4bd5af40ceddc9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Suraj P Kizhakkethil <quic_surapk@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 27 Feb 2025 17:05:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 136/141] wifi: mac80211: Fix EAPOL failure when 802.3 encap
 offload enabled

Currently, when the driver supports 802.3 encap offload, EAPOL packets are
transmitted in Ethernet format. mac80211 queues these packets to the Tx
queue. While handling these queued packets, 802.3 frames are interpreted as
802.11 frames, and 802.11 header checks are performed. This causes mac80211
to drop these packets. mac80211's current implementation assumes that if
the driver supports 802.3 encap offload, it should also support 802.11
packets on the same interface. Due to this assumption, EAPOL packets are
getting dropped, causing EAPOL handshake failures. To fix this issue,
bypass the assumption by directly passing the EAPOL packets to the driver
Tx callback. This avoids the packet drop and prevents EAPOL handshake
failures, as the ath12k firmware does not enable per-packet encap type.

Co-developed-by: P Praneesh <quic_ppranees@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <quic_ppranees@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Suraj P Kizhakkethil <quic_surapk@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Raj Kumar Bhagat <quic_rajkbhag@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Johnson <jeff.johnson@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 net/mac80211/tx.c | 15 ++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/tx.c b/net/mac80211/tx.c
index 221ccd169862..90c050dcef22 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/tx.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/tx.c
@@ -4593,7 +4593,20 @@ static bool ieee80211_tx_8023(struct ieee80211_sub_if_data *sdata,
 {
 	struct ieee80211_local *local = sdata->local;
 	struct sk_buff *next;
-	bool ret = true;
+	struct ieee80211_tx_control control = {};
+	struct ieee80211_sta *pubsta = NULL;
+	struct ethhdr *ehdr = (struct ethhdr *)skb->data;
+	bool ret = true, is_eapol;
+
+	is_eapol = (sdata->control_port_protocol == ehdr->h_proto);
+	if (sta && is_eapol) {
+		if (sta->uploaded)
+			pubsta = &sta->sta;
+
+		control.sta = pubsta;
+		drv_tx(local, &control, skb);
+		return ret;
+	}
 
 	if (ieee80211_queue_skb(local, sdata, sta, skb))
 		return true;
-- 
